Operate the program as following:
1. Open the terminal
2. go to the directory containing the program (by $ cd …)
3. type command “make clean”
4. type command “make build”
5. type command “make check T=t X=x N=n” (example: “make check T=5 X=2 N=12”)
   (t is number of threads you want to create in thread pool (> 0)
    x is power x of e^x you want to calculate
    n is the number of terms you want to expend to estimate the e^x)
6. get the result